The paper discusses requirements engineering and user involvement in the development of mobile apps, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of the Wizard of Oz technique and user reviews also suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The analysis of app reviews involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The potential for communication gaps and the need for risk mitigation align with the cybersecurity (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SI) categories.
